===========================================================================
Clean-room attribution
===========================================================================

This library is a clean-room re-implementation of the FT8 decoder and
encoder algorithms in Go. No source code from WSJT-X, JTDX, or any other
GPL-licensed project is included in this repository. All .go source files
are original work, derived from study of the published FT8/FT4 protocol
specification and the public WSJT-X 2.7.0 Fortran reference.

The Go source files are licensed under MIT (see LICENSE). The FT8/FT4
protocol itself is documented in:

  Taylor, Joseph H. (K1JT); Walker, Steven J. (W9MDB); et al.
  "The FT4 and FT8 Communication Protocols", QEX July/August 2020.
  https://wsjt.sourceforge.io/FT4_FT8_QEX.pdf

===========================================================================
Developer-only diagnostic tooling
===========================================================================

The Fortran programs under internal/fortran_test/ are developer-only
diagnostic tools used to compare the Go implementation against the WSJT-X
2.7.0 reference. They call WSJT-X subroutines at compile time via static
linking against the GPLv3 WSJT-X source tree.

The .f90 source files under internal/fortran_test/ are our own work
(subroutine calls, parameter setup, and I/O; no copied WSJT-X code) and
are licensed under MIT along with the rest of this repository.

The compiled binaries produced from these .f90 sources are GPLv3-licensed
by inheritance from WSJT-X and MUST NOT be distributed. These binaries are
produced in a temporary directory and never committed to this repository
(see internal/fortran_test/.gitignore).

